Map<String,Object> ctx = new LinkedHashMap<>();
ctx.put("_etag", previousETag);
ctx.put("readAtUtc", java.time.OffsetDateTime.now().toString());
// if you capture _lsn or others, add them here

// Optional sessions: ONLY pass docId if your queue is session-enabled; else pass null
String sessionId = Boolean.parseBoolean(System.getenv("ServiceBusUseSessions")) ? docId : null;

// For each matched event, send one message
for (EventConfig.Event evt : eventsFired) {
    MessageBus.sendEvent(
        cosmosDbContainerName,     // container
        id,                        // docId
        evt.id,                    // eventId
        evt.name,                  // eventName
        when,                      // "insert" | "update"
        deltas,                    // your tracked field changes (empty on insert is OK)
        ctx,                       // context map
        sessionId,                 // null if sessions disabled or queue not session-enabled
        newDoc,                    // for ErrorWriter on failure
        ERROR_CONTAINER,           // your BlobContainerClient for errors
        context.getLogger()        // function logger
    );
}

Do I need to close the sender?
	•	No, not per message/invocation. Reuse the cached sender. The Functions host will close sockets on shutdown.
	•	If you insist on explicit closing, call ServiceBusClientHolder.closeAll() from a shutdown hook. It’s optional.

